SUMMARY:Food\, Climate and Conflict: From Control to Annihilation of Food
  Systems in Gaza - by Dalla Lana School of Public Health
LOCATION:Virtual
DESCRIPTION:More info:
  https://www.eventbrite.ca/e/food-climate-conflict-from-control-to-annihil
 ation-in-gaza-tickets-1980214824847\n\nHosted by Dalla Lana School of
  Public Health (https://www.dlsph.utoronto.ca/)\n\nThis talk examines the
  long history of food system control in Palestine\, including through
  constraints on climate adaptation efforts\, and argues that what has
  unfolded in Gaza since 2023 represents a profound shift from mechanisms
  of control and constraint to the systematic annihilation of the food
  system and local ecologies.
END:VEVENT
