SUMMARY:FilmSocial: Norma Rae - by Leo Panitch School for Socialist
  Education
LOCATION:Eyesore Cinema
DESCRIPTION:More info:
  https://www.tickettailor.com/events/panitchschool/2104533\n\nHosted by
  Leo Panitch School for Socialist Education
  (https://leopanitchschool.ca/)\n\nThis screening is part of the Leo
  Panitch School’s FilmSocial series of socialist film screenings. Norma
  Rae tells the story of a courageous worker and single mother who risks
  her job\, relationships\, and community to stand up to the bosses and
  organize her fellow workers at a crushing textile mill. Based on a real
  story of labour organizer Crystal Lee Sutton.
END:VEVENT
