SUMMARY:Quebec 2012: How a Student Strike Brought Down the Government - by
  Revolutionary Communist Party Toronto
LOCATION:285 Victoria St\, Room VIC-608
DESCRIPTION:More info: https://www.instagram.com/p/DWDDGRXFe3E/\n\nHosted
  by Revolutionary Communist Party Toronto
  (https://www.instagram.com/toronto_communist/)\n\nIn 2012\, Quebec
  students went on a months-long strike to reverse a planned 75 per cent
  tuition increase. It ended with the fall of the provincial government and
  the cancellation of the tuition hike. Come learn how this movement was
  able to win\, and how students can build a movement just like it today.
END:VEVENT
